	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Poppah, since you started this thread, and I feel you have some right to have your point directly addressed, I will do so.<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">My original point had nothing to do with the EULA. If you are really feel adimant about the EULA that is fine. There is nothing I can say about that. </td></tr></table><br />
That is true.  But the title of your post is not "Buying PP is not a waste of $$"  The title of your post is "PP buying not bad"<br />
<br />
As far "feeling adamant" about the Eula, them's the rules.  It's not something where feelings really matter.  But yes, many of the players here are rule-abiding gamers.<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">My point was aside from that people tend to frown on people buying pp ( because it is a waste of money )even though they do the same thing just in other ways.<br />
