</td></tr></table><br />
<br />
Here I will totally and wholeheartedly agree with you.  PP buying is not bad because it is a waste of money.  People can roll their money up into cigarettes and smoke it for all I care.  On a utilarian ground, one might say it would be better to buy $150 worth each year of platinum, rather than a second account.  <br />
<br />
My objection to PP buying has nothing to do with the fact that it's a waste of money.  In fact, at the prices it's at now, $1 = 1kpp, it's a rather good deal.<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">P.S. In my original post I said that pp duping is wrong. </td></tr></table><br />
