	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">To Moonsorrow: I do not know how to take quotes out like you guys do so I am going to quote for you.<br />
<br />
I agreed with most everything you said except one thing. That buying pp ( not duped ) does not hurt <br />
<br />
the EQ economy but just changes hands. You disagreed. I do not feel like it does hurt the economy. <br />
<br />
How could it? The money was already there. If I didn't buy something with that money someone else <br />
<br />
would. And items raised recently due to a dupe. Not pp buying from someone who killed gnolls all day <br />
<br />
long. In fact the fact that newbies cant obtain high level items anymore? That can't be true because this <br />
<br />
is countered by items coming into the economy now. I have played this came since the month it came <br />
<br />
out and the items that were "Uber" then don't compare to what newbies run around with now. I had a 44 <br />
<br />
cleric within the first 4 months of EQ coming out and the most sought out weapon was the SSoY. 8 dmg<br />
<br />
24 dly 1hs. with a proc. You almost had to almost be lvl 50 to even think about getting this item and it sold for around 4k pp. Now you would be lucky to get 200pp for a 8 - 24 weapon. heck the centi <br />
<br />
shortsword is better than this and can be bought easily for 200pp. Wearing banded till you are almost <br />
<br />
40 is all but unheard of now however that was the norm back then. If someone complains about there armor I guarantee you that I paid more for crappier stuff at a higher lvl. And stuff running 500 to 800pp <br />
<br />
for a 4 wis bloodstained tunic was normal and the mobs still dropped the same amount of pp. It wasn't <br />
<br />
any easier for me back then I promise. Yet I still managed to enjoy the game and be able to play today.<br />
<br />
P.S. Yes maybe this should have been in Rants and raves. Sorry <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="Frown"> <br />
