	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">you have yet to show that buying and selling platinum is a morally wrong action in and of itself. Because the purchase of platinum encourages cheating does not make the purchase inherently wrong.</td></tr></table> <br />
<br />
Varyx,<br />
<br />
In your post *You* prove that it is wrong.<br />
<br />
Lets use the following quote in your post and then apply them to some basic rules of logic. That being if A=B and B=C, Therefore A=C<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">Hacking and cheating *are* wrong</td></tr></table><br />
<br />
Buying/Selling Plat for RL dollars is a vilotion of the EULA, and thus a violation of the game. If you do it you break the rules of the game, ie, you are cheating.<br />
<br />
If buying/selling plat is cheating, and cheating is wrong, therefore, buying/selling plat is wrong.<br />
<br />
It's about as basic as that.<br />
<br />
As far as a couple of other things. The plat duping schemes can be considered the equivelent of counterfeiting. In effect what these people were doing was counterfeiting Platinum. The reason the EQ economy got screwed up was because a mass amount of counterfeit cash was introduced into the economy. This follows the theories of many economic principals. Ask any economist and they will tell you that a mass influx of counterfeit money into a capitalist economy will devalue that dollar and cause mass inflation in prices. SOE had to step in, just like the US Dept. of Treasury would step in and squash anyone counterfeiting the US dollar.<br />
<br />
As to why SOE does not squash someone like Yantis? Ask your self this and you will find the answer if you are a logical thinking being: In order for Yantis to do what he does, how many accounts does he hold on each server? And how many servers are  there? And how many others like Yantis are out there? You do the math and it all adds up to one thing. $$$<br />
<br />
At the risk of being ridiculed, I will use a quote from Rush Limbaugh. You may agree/disagree with him, hate him, love him, whatever. But the following statement he made is one thing almost anyone can agree with, and I paraphrase: If you want to get to the ultimate truth of ANYTHING, follow the money trail.</font></p>
	
